sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Scar25 ATG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is produced by an assembly method.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence is produced by RFC10-assembly of a RFC10-RBS with a RFC25-prefixed part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The resulting sequence is a combination of the RFC10 RBS-CDS scar (tactag) and 9 nucleotides from the RFC25 prefix (atg gcc ggc).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Osthege

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Scar 25
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is the scar produced by assembly using RFC 25.
If you are assembling a composite part using RFC 25, you can insert this part and specify blunt assembly to get the desired sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1321002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Re-entry of BBa_K863111, Cellulose Binding Domain CBDclos in rfc25
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is a direct copy of BBa_K863111 with slight modifications to the beginning and end of the sequence for the purposes of allowing composite parts to be added correctly using this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a copy of BBa_K863111 (Cellulose binding domain of C. cellulovorans cellulose binding protein gene (Freiburg-Standard)) and was created only as a registry entry, removing the atg-NgoMIV parts at the front and the AgeI-taa basepairs from the sequence so that the registry does not flag it as rfc25 incompatible, and it enables us to enter fusion proteins with this part as automatic composite parts in the method as described by: http://2009.igem.org/Team:Freiburg_bioware/general.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is a direct copy of BBa_K863111 with slight modifications to the beginning and end of the sequence for the purposes of allowing composite parts to be added correctly using this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xenia Spencer-Milnes

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1321009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is based on the existing BioBrick BBa_K1151001 by the 2013 Salente Lecce iGEM team.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Nickel Binding Protein in Freiburg format (RFC 25) to allow for easy use in fusion proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: OEPCR primers were designed to allow for the replacement of the standard BioBrick prefix and suffix with the Freiburg prefix and suffix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris N Micklem
